Columns: 1;
                                                  ruled lines: 10 26;
                                                  written lines: 10 26; Uniform codex. The codex is called the Golden Haggadah because of the diapered gold-leaf background of its miniatures.
Ruling is visible. Hair-side and flesh-side of the folios are distinguishable.
Erased text (e. g. folios 81r, 83r, 86r, 86v, 87r, 90v, 94v, 95r, 97r). Many illustrations, which consist mainly of gold, silver, and occasionally coloured letters of first and striking words, placed within coloured designs.
